  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>All your usual continental breakfast classics greet you each morning. For dinner, enjoy four varied courses with options to choose. Antipasti and salad buffets partner menu selections. Spending the holidays here? Christmas and New Year gala style dinners are included. </p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>1</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p>We're sure you'll really enjoy the mountain style and warm feel at Hotel La Betulla. The friendly staff play a big part in creating that atmosphere, nothing's too much trouble for them. Although it's not right on the slopes, access to them is great. The bus stop for the free resort bus is just outside, where there's a regular service to and from Campo Smith and the main lifts. If you want to explore the <span>Jafferau ski area, the bus there stops just around the corner. And i</span>t's only a short stroll into the historic old town of <a data-udi="umb://document/632726451b0d4569b6f2cd0d56b628c3" href="/{localLink:umb://document/632726451b0d4569b6f2cd0d56b628c3}" title="Bardonecchia">Bardonecchia</a>. We found it a nice way to stretch the legs after long days of carving up the piste or making the most of the snow fields.</p>
<p>The lounge bar area is really great for the casual, apres ski social. We loved catching up with new friends and finding out what they got up to during the day. Dinner is in the cosy dining area, where you'll be served tasty regional and Italian dishes complete with antipasto and a salad buffet. The breakfast buffet has a good selection to get you ready for an action packed day. When its time to rest up after a long day on the mountains you'll find your room comfortable and nicely decorated. Some have lovely views of the Alps.</p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 1 hour 30 mins by coach from Turin airport.</p>]]></description>
